elapsed_ms":0,"fired":false,"rule_id":"USDPA-023","rule_version":"1.0.0"},{"elapsed_ms":0,"fired":false,"rule_id":"USDPA-024","rule_version":"1.0.0"},{"elapsed_ms":0,"fired":false,"rule_id":"USDPA-025","rule_version":"1.0.0"}],"findings":[{"description":"No clause was found defining the duration of confidentiality obligations.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(clause absent from the document)"},"explanation":"Industry consensus and UTSA practice require an explicit confidentiality term. Without one, the duration is ambiguous and may not be enforceable in some jurisdictions.","id":"NDA-D-003-s1-0","recommendation":"Add a clause stating either a definite term (e.g., 5 years from disclosure) or, preferably, a definite term for confidential information plus a perpetual term for trade secrets.","rule_id":"NDA-D-003","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"critical","source_citations":[{"id":"utsa-1985","license":"Public uniform-law text","license_url":"https://www.uniformlaws.org/HigherLogic/System/DownloadDocumentFile.ashx?DocumentFileKey=e19b2528-e0b1-0054-23c4-8069701a4b62","retrieved_at":"2026-05-12T00:00:00Z","source":"Uniform Trade Secrets Act (UTSA) (1985 amended)","source_url":"https://www.uniformlaws.org/committees/community-home?CommunityKey=3a2538fb-e030-4e2d-a9e2-90373dc05792"}],"title":"Confidentiality term clause missing"},{"description":"Confidential-Information definition lacks an exclusion for information previously known to the receiving party.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(clause absent from the document)"},"explanation":"Without a 'previously known' carve-out, the receiver risks breaching the NDA by using information they already possessed.","id":"NDA-D-007-s1-0","recommendation":"Add: 'Confidential Information does not include information already known to Receiving Party prior to disclosure, as evidenced by its written records.'","rule_id":"NDA-D-007","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"critical","source_citations":[{"id":"nda-consensus-drafting","license":"Common Paper Standard NDA, CC BY 4.0","license_url":"https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/","retrieved_at":"2026-05-12T00:00:00Z","source":"Consensus NDA drafting practice (Common Paper, ACC, ABA practice notes)","source_url":"https://commonpaper.com/standards/mutual-nda/"}],"title":"'Already known' exclusion missing"},{"description":"No clause was found requiring return or destruction of Confidential Information.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(clause absent from the document)"},"explanation":"Without this clause the discloser has no contractual hook to recover or wipe disclosed material once the relationship ends.","id":"NDA-D-013-s1-0","recommendation":"Add a return-or-destruction clause triggered by termination of the NDA or upon written request by Disclosing Party.","rule_id":"NDA-D-013","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"critical","source_citations":[{"id":"nda-consensus-drafting","license":"Common Paper Standard NDA, CC BY 4.0","license_url":"https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/","retrieved_at":"2026-05-12T00:00:00Z","source":"Consensus NDA drafting practice (Common Paper, ACC, ABA practice notes)","source_url":"https://commonpaper.com/standards/mutual-nda/"}],"title":"Return-or-destruction clause missing"},{"description":"No clause was found acknowledging irreparable harm or entitlement to injunctive relief.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(clause absent from the document)"},"explanation":"Without an irreparable-harm acknowledgment, a court may require the discloser to prove inadequate-remedy-at-law from scratch, slowing emergency relief in a leak scenario.","id":"NDA-D-015-s1-0","recommendation":"Add: 'The parties agree that monetary damages would be an inadequate remedy for any breach of this Agreement and that the non-breaching party shall be entitled to seek injunctive or other equitable relief, in addition to any other available remedies.'","rule_id":"NDA-D-015","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"critical","source_citations":[{"id":"nda-consensus-drafting","license":"Common Paper Standard NDA, CC BY 4.0","license_url":"https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/","retrieved_at":"2026-05-12T00:00:00Z","source":"Consensus NDA drafting practice (Common Paper, ACC, ABA practice notes)","source_url":"https://commonpaper.com/standards/mutual-nda/"}],"title":"Injunctive-relief clause missing"},{"description":"The contract does not allocate ownership of intellectual property.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(no IP-ownership clause)"},"explanation":"Without an IP-ownership clause, default copyright and patent rules apply: under 17 U.S.C. § 201, copyright vests in the author/employee unless work-for-hire or assignment applies.","id":"IPDATA-001-s1-0","rule_id":"IPDATA-001","rule_version":"1.2.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[{"id":"stat-17-usc-101","license":"Public domain (US government work)","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-11T00:00:00Z","source":"17 U.S.C. § 101 — Definitions (work made for hire)","source_url":"https://www.law.cornell.edu/uscode/text/17/101"},{"id":"stat-17-usc-201","license":"Public domain (US government work)","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-11T00:00:00Z","source":"17 U.S.C. § 201","source_url":"https://www.law.cornell.edu/uscode/text/17/201"}],"title":"No IP-ownership clause detected"},{"description":"No clause was found extending the confidentiality obligation for trade secrets beyond the fixed term.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(clause absent from the document)"},"explanation":"If the NDA imposes a flat 3- or 5-year confidentiality term with no carve-out for trade secrets, the discloser loses statutory protection once the term lapses — defeating the purpose of UTSA / DTSA.","id":"NDA-D-004-s1-0","recommendation":"Add: 'With respect to trade secrets, the obligations of confidentiality shall continue for as long as the information qualifies as a trade secret under applicable law.'","rule_id":"NDA-D-004","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[{"id":"utsa-1985","license":"Public uniform-law text","license_url":"https://www.uniformlaws.org/HigherLogic/System/DownloadDocumentFile.ashx?DocumentFileKey=e19b2528-e0b1-0054-23c4-8069701a4b62","retrieved_at":"2026-05-12T00:00:00Z","source":"Uniform Trade Secrets Act (UTSA) (1985 amended)","source_url":"https://www.uniformlaws.org/committees/community-home?CommunityKey=3a2538fb-e030-4e2d-a9e2-90373dc05792"}],"title":"Trade-secret perpetual carve-out missing"},{"description":"Return-or-destruction language was detected but does not require written certification of destruction.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(clause absent from the document)"},"explanation":"Without an attestation requirement, the discloser has no proof that destruction actually occurred — a real-world enforcement gap.","id":"NDA-D-014-s1-0","recommendation":"Add: 'Receiving Party shall provide a written certification, signed by an officer, attesting to compliance with this Section within thirty (30) days.'","rule_id":"NDA-D-014","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[{"id":"nda-consensus-drafting","license":"Common Paper Standard NDA, CC BY 4.0","license_url":"https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/","retrieved_at":"2026-05-12T00:00:00Z","source":"Consensus NDA drafting practice (Common Paper, ACC, ABA practice notes)","source_url":"https://commonpaper.com/standards/mutual-nda/"}],"title":"Return-or-destruction attestation missing"},{"description":"Injunctive-relief clause does not include a waiver of bond.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(clause absent from the document)"},"explanation":"Many courts require a movant to post a bond as a condition of preliminary injunctive relief. A contractual waiver smooths the emergency-motion path.","id":"NDA-D-016-s1-0","recommendation":"Add: 'The party seeking injunctive relief shall be entitled to such relief without the need to post a bond or other security.'","rule_id":"NDA-D-016","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[{"id":"nda-consensus-drafting","license":"Common Paper Standard NDA, CC BY 4.0","license_url":"https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/","retrieved_at":"2026-05-12T00:00:00Z","source":"Consensus NDA drafting practice (Common Paper, ACC, ABA practice notes)","source_url":"https://commonpaper.com/standards/mutual-nda/"}],"title":"Waiver-of-bond language missing"},{"description":"No representation of authority or absence of conflicting obligations was found.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(clause absent from the document)"},"explanation":"An authority representation is a low-cost addition that closes off a defensive argument later. Common Paper includes it.","id":"NDA-D-022-s1-0","recommendation":"Add: 'Each party represents that it has full authority to enter into this Agreement and that doing so does not conflict with any other obligation.'","rule_id":"NDA-D-022","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[{"id":"nda-consensus-drafting","license":"Common Paper Standard NDA, CC BY 4.0","license_url":"https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/","retrieved_at":"2026-05-12T00:00:00Z","source":"Consensus NDA drafting practice (Common Paper, ACC, ABA practice notes)","source_url":"https://commonpaper.com/standards/mutual-nda/"}],"title":"Authority / no-conflicting-obligation representation missing"},{"description":"Neither 'indemnify' nor 'hold harmless' appears in the document.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(no indemnification language)"},"explanation":"Most commercial contracts allocate risk through an indemnification clause. The absence leaves the parties to default tort and contract law for any third-party claims.","id":"RISK-001-s1-0","rule_id":"RISK-001","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[],"title":"No indemnification clause detected"},{"description":"Vaulytica did not find a limitation-of-liability clause.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(no LoL clause)"},"explanation":"Without a limitation-of-liability clause, exposure is bounded only by what the parties can prove in damages. Most commercial contracts cap liability.","id":"RISK-005-s1-0","rule_id":"RISK-005","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[],"title":"No limitation-of-liability clause detected"},{"description":"The contract does not state a path to terminate for material breach.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(no for-cause termination)"},"explanation":"Without a for-cause termination path, parties must rely on common-law material-breach doctrines, which are jurisdiction-dependent.","id":"TERM-002-s1-0","rule_id":"TERM-002","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[],"title":"No termination-for-cause clause detected"},{"description":"No clause was found stating that the NDA does not establish precedent for future agreements.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(clause absent from the document)"},"explanation":"A no-precedent clause prevents the receiver from arguing that prior NDAs control subsequent commercial-deal drafting. Optional but common.","id":"NDA-D-019-s1-0","recommendation":"Add: 'This Agreement is not intended to create, and shall not be construed as creating, a precedent for any future agreement between the parties.'","rule_id":"NDA-D-019","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[{"id":"nda-consensus-drafting","license":"Common Paper Standard NDA, CC BY 4.0","license_url":"https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/","retrieved_at":"2026-05-12T00:00:00Z","source":"Consensus NDA drafting practice (Common Paper, ACC, ABA practice notes)","source_url":"https://commonpaper.com/standards/mutual-nda/"}],"title":"No-precedent / no-MFN clause missing"},{"description":"Only receiving party bears this typically-mutual obligation.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"confidentiality obligation"},"explanation":"Obligations like confidentiality, indemnity, and representations are usually mutual. A one-sided version is sometimes intentional but worth confirming.","id":"OBLI-002-s1-0","rule_id":"OBLI-002","rule_version":"1.1.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[],"title":"Asymmetric confidentiality obligation"},{"description":"§ 1833(b), an employee shall not be held criminally or civilly liable under any Federal or State trade secret law for th","document_position":2727,"excerpt":{"end_offset":3231,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":2727,"text":"§ 1833(b), an employee shall not be held criminally or civilly liable under any Federal or State trade secret law for the disclosure of a trade secret that — (A) is made (i) in confidence to a Federal, State, or local government official, either directly or indirectly, or to an attorney; and (ii) solely for the purpose of reporting or investigating a suspected violation of law; or (B) is made in a complaint or other document filed in a lawsuit or other proceeding, if such filing is made under seal."},"explanation":"Negative covenants restrict what a party may do. Surfacing them collectively makes it easier to check they are intended and consistent with the overall deal.","id":"OBLI-005-s1-2727","rule_id":"OBLI-005","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[],"title":"Negative covenants: 1"},{"description":"Confidential Information","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"Confidential Information"},"explanation":"Defined terms should be capitalized identically wherever they appear. A lowercase use of a defined term reads as ordinary usage and can change the meaning.","id":"STRUCT-009-s1-0","rule_id":"STRUCT-009","rule_version":"1.4.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[],"title":"Inconsistent capitalization for 1 defined term"},{"description":"1 reference uses the lowercase form of a defined term — likely a drafting slip. Affected terms: \"Confidential Information\".","document_position":349,"excerpt":{"end_offset":373,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":349,"text":"Confidential Information"},"explanation":"A defined term carries its contractual meaning only when it is referenced with the same casing as its definition. A lowercase occurrence either creates a genuine ambiguity (the reader cannot tell if the defined meaning was intended) or signals a missed capitalization. Courts in commercial drafting jurisdictions sometimes read lowercase variants as the plain-English meaning rather than the defined meaning.","id":"STRUCT-014-s1-349","recommendation":"Recapitalize each lowercase occurrence to match the defined casing, or remove the term entirely if the unaltered plain-English meaning was intended.","rule_id":"STRUCT-014","rule_version":"1.2.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[],"title":"Defined terms used in lowercase: 1"},{"description":"Upon termination of this Agreement or upon written request by the Disclosing Party, the Receiving Party shall promptly return","document_position":3634,"excerpt":{"end_offset":3759,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":3634,"text":"6. Return or Destruction. Upon termination of this Agreement or upon written request by the Disclosing Party, the Receiving Party shall promptly return to the Disclosing Party or destroy all Confidential Information in the Receiving Party's possession or control, including all co"},"explanation":"Post-termination obligations typically include return or destruction of confidential materials, deletion of data, and a certificate of destruction.","id":"TERM-007-s1-3634","rule_id":"TERM-007","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[],"title":"Post-termination obligations enumerated"}],"playbook_id":"unilateral-nda-deep","playbook_match_confidence":1,"playbook_match_reasoning":"forced via sidecar to unilateral-nda-deep","result_hash":"07bf5d1040d9dc67648ba2facc5fee3dd94339b48fd0ee40fc9742e41db9bf20","source_file":{"name":"unilateral-nda-deep-missing-term-fail.txt","sha256":"18959fa9c467421a70c2932dad0862102029ddd7fc7c079bef68148c801b1a8e","size_bytes":1},"version":"9.41.0"}